ition of glair \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/glair\">glair</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of hale \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/hale#etymonline_v_1386\">hale</a> (v.); <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of halyard \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/halyard\">halyard</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of intercalate \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/intercalate\">intercalate</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of haul \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/haul\">haul</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of keelhaul \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/keelhaul\">keelhaul</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of low \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/low#etymonline_v_14562\">low</a> (v.); <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of nomenclature \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/nomenclature\">nomenclature</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of paraclete \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/paraclete\">paraclete</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of proclaim \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/proclaim\">proclaim</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of reclaim \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/reclaim\">reclaim</a>; <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of reconcile \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/reconcile\">reconcile</a>。</p><p>它是以下词语的假设来源/其存在的证据由以下提供：梵语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">usakala</i> “公鸡”，字面意思是“黎明呼唤”； 拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">calare</i> “庄严宣布，呼喊”， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">clamare</i> “大声喊叫，呼喊，宣布”； 中古爱尔兰语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">cailech</i> “公鸡”； 希腊语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">kalein</i> “叫喊”， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">kela